original: Höglund, Tom Artur Hjalmar, ’skeppsmäklare, Kalmar, f. 9/3/09 i Kalmar av skeppsmäklare Hjalmar H. o. Agnes Wikander. G. 41 m. Gunvor Sjöberg. Barn: Leif f. 42, Ann-Louise 45. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 27. Stud. i Engl. 30-31 o. i Tyskl. 35-36, res. t. Danzig, Polen, Litauen, Lettland o. Finl. Skeppsmäklare i A-B Bröd. Höglund i Kalmar sed. 33, huv:-redare i Rederibol. Grims’kär i Kalmar sed. 47. Led. av styr. f. A-B Bröd. Höglund sed. 33 o. i A-B Motorkraft i Sthlm sed. 35, -sekr. i Kalmar tennis-kl. sed. 44. Hobbies: tennis, bridge, konst.
translated: Höglund, Tom Artur Hjalmar, ship broker, Kalmar, born March 9th, 1909 in Kalmar to ship broker Hjalmar H. and Agnes Wikander. Married in 1941 to Gunvor Sjöberg. Children: Leif born in 1942, Ann-Louise born in 1945. He graduated from high school in Kalmar in 1927. He studied in England from 1930-1931 and in Germany from 1935-1936, traveling to Danzig, Poland, Lithuania, Latvia, and Finland. He has worked as a ship broker for A-B Bröd. Höglund in Kalmar since 1933, and as a principal owner of Rederibol. Grims’kär in Kalmar since 1947. He has been a board member of A-B Bröd. Höglund since 1933 and of A-B Motorkraft in Stockholm since 1935. He served as secretary for the Kalmar Tennis Club since 1944. His hobbies include tennis, bridge, and art.
